{"parse":{"title":"Short-arm inspection","pageid":25627238,"revid":796383701,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg/220px-Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"163\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg/330px-Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg/440px-Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"593\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Recruit%27s_Progress-_Medical_Inspection_Art.IWMARTLD2909.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Painting by <a href=\"/wiki/Carel_Weight\" title=\"Carel Weight\">Carel Weight</a> of British Army recruits undergoing medical inspection, 1942 (<a href=\"/wiki/Imperial_War_Museum\" title=\"Imperial War Museum\">Imperial War Museum</a> art collection)</div></div></div>\n<p>The term \"<b>short-arm inspection</b>\" is a <a href=\"/wiki/Military\" title=\"Military\">military</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Euphemism\" title=\"Euphemism\">euphemism</a> referring to the routine medical inspection of male soldiers' <a href=\"/wiki/Penis\" title=\"Penis\">penises</a> (\"short arms\") for signs of <a href=\"/wiki/Sexually-transmitted_disease\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sexually-transmitted disease\">sexually-transmitted diseases</a> and other medical problems.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The precise origin of the term is uncertain; however, American<sup id=\"cite_ref-Evans_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Evans-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/wiki/Australian\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Australian\">Australian</a> troops are known to have used the term during the <a href=\"/wiki/First_World_War\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"First World War\">First World War</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Examples\">Examples</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Short-arm_inspection&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Examples\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The practice within the <a href=\"/wiki/Imperial_Japanese_Army\" title=\"Imperial Japanese Army\">Imperial Japanese Army</a> during World War 2 was described by an anonymous American soldier, who had been forced to work as a truck driver while held as a prisoner of war, and who came into daily close contact with Japanese soldiers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303468\">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 40px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class=\"templatequote\"><p>When a Jap G.I. turns in with a venereal disease, he gets a good beating and loses what few privileges have been allowed to him. For this reason, they go to civilian doctors or to drug stores, and try to doctor themselves. Many of them are infected. Short-arm inspection is held only on rare occasions. In fact, there was only one such inspection during the time I was a prisoner.</p><div class=\"templatequotecite\">\u2014&#8201;<cite>American, former prisoner of war (1945)</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Short-arm_inspection&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/short%20arm%20inspection\">merriam-webster.com</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Evans-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Evans_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Evans, Martin Marix (2014). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=I8K2AgAAQBAJ&amp;dq=short+arm+inspection+wwi&amp;source=gbs_navlinks_s\"><i>American Voices of World War I: Primary Source Documents, 1917-1920</i></a>. Routledge. pp.&#160;11\u201312. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1135969787\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1135969787\">1135969787</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 September</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+Voices+of+World+War+I%3A+Primary+Source+Documents%2C+1917-1920&amp;rft.pages=11-12&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft.isbn=1135969787&amp;rft.aulast=Evans&amp;rft.aufirst=Martin+Marix&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DI8K2AgAAQBAJ%26dq%3Dshort%2Barm%2Binspection%2Bwwi%26source%3Dgbs_navlinks_s&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AShort-arm+inspection\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20070522093343/http://www.anu.edu.au/andc/res/aus_words/wwi/S.php\">Glossary of WWI slang: S</a>, at the Australian National Dictionary Centre (via <a href=\"/wiki/Archive.org\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archive.org\">archive.org</a>); version archived May 22, 2007</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/1945-01IntelligenceBulletinVol03No05#page/n1/mode/2up\">\"The Japanese G.I.\"</a> <i>Intelligence Bulletin</i>. Military Intelligence Service, War Department. <b>III</b> (5): 9. January 1945.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Intelligence+Bulletin&amp;rft.atitle=The+Japanese+G.I.&amp;rft.volume=III&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=9&amp;rft.date=1945-01&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2F1945-01IntelligenceBulletinVol03No05%23page%2Fn1%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AShort-arm+inspection\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1327\nCached time: 20180902032314\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.088 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.123 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 201/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 4219/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 